covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval with various parameter combinations (TC01, TC02, TC05).
Empty Response / No Results: Scenarios for empty results (TC06, TC24).
Pagination: Several scenarios exercise offset/limit behavior (TC02, TC05, TC07, TC08, TC26).
Query Parameters: Multiple valid/invalid parameter combinations tested (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC08, TC09-TC13, TC16-TC18, TC20-TC21, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27).
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid tokens (TC13, TC14).
Error Handling: Tests for client errors, server errors, and timeout scenarios (TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC16, TC25).
Performance/Concurrency: Concurrent requests (TC20) and large data volume (TC19) and high limit tests (TC26).
Data integrity / audit detail: Audit parameter variations (TC03, TC04, TC05).
gaps: Pagination: While several tests exist, explicit validation of paging boundaries with extremely large datasets and correct page boundaries could be more explicit (e.g., exact items returned for given offset/limit).
Caching Behavior: No tests assert caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation semantics.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior.
Authorization: While 401 cases are covered, no test distinguishes between 401 vs 403 where applicable (if applicable to API).
Partial/Edge invalid inputs: Some edge cases around malformed searchKey could be broadened (beyond basic invalid characters).
UI accessibility: TC22 is included but depends on UI existence; if UI isn’t present in all environments, this may be optional.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation behavior.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure system handles bursts or high-frequency requests.
Consider explicit 403 authorization scenario if applicable (beyond 401).
Enhance pagination coverage with precise boundary checks on large datasets (verify exact subset returned for given offset/limit).
Keep or expand accessibility tests if a UI client exists; otherwise, align with API-only accessibility checks (e.g., machine-readable response accessibility considerations).
